      • getNewDatatypeHandler

        protected abstract DatatypeHandler getNewDatatypeHandler()
        Generates a new instance of the DatatypeHandler implementation in question and returns it.
        Returns:
        A new instance of the DatatypeHandler implementation being tested.

      • getRecognisedDatatypeUri

        protected abstract URI getRecognisedDatatypeUri()
        Returns:
        A URI that must return true from DatatypeHandler.isRecognizedDatatype(URI) and not throw an exception if used with a valid value when calling DatatypeHandler.verifyDatatype(String, URI) and DatatypeHandler.normalizeDatatype(String, URI, ValueFactory) .

      • getUnrecognisedDatatypeUri

        protected abstract URI getUnrecognisedDatatypeUri()
        Returns:
        A URI that must return false from DatatypeHandler.isRecognizedDatatype(URI) and throw an exception if used with DatatypeHandler.verifyDatatype(String, URI) and DatatypeHandler.normalizeDatatype(String, URI, ValueFactory) .

      • getValueMatchingRecognisedDatatypeUri

        protected abstract String getValueMatchingRecognisedDatatypeUri()
        Returns:
        A string value that does match the recognised datatype URI, and will succeed when used with both DatatypeHandler.verifyDatatype(String, URI) and DatatypeHandler.normalizeDatatype(String, URI, ValueFactory) .

      • getValueNotMatchingRecognisedDatatypeUri

        protected abstract String getValueNotMatchingRecognisedDatatypeUri()
        Returns:
        A string value that does not match the recognised datatype URI, and will fail when used with both DatatypeHandler.verifyDatatype(String, URI) and DatatypeHandler.normalizeDatatype(String, URI, ValueFactory) .

      • getNormalisedLiteralForRecognisedDatatypeAndValue

        protected abstract Literal getNormalisedLiteralForRecognisedDatatypeAndValue()
        Returns:
        An instance of Literal that is equal to the expected output from a successful call to DatatypeHandler.normalizeDatatype(String, URI, org.openrdf.model.ValueFactory) ;

      • getValueFactory

        protected abstract ValueFactory getValueFactory()
        Returns:
        An instance of ValueFactory that can be used to produce a normalised literal.

      • getExpectedKey

        protected abstract String getExpectedKey()
        Returns:
        The key that is expected to be returned for DatatypeHandler.getKey() to identify the service.
